CHINA’S CENTRAL government has made an example of Cathay Pacific, the huge Hong Kong-based airline. Will the ploy work to quell protests in the territory, or just further rattle the nerves of international firms? Also, we examine the spectacular rise of Pentecostalism in Ethiopia and its effects on the country’s politics. And we explain the plight of puffins on the Faroe Islands. Runtime: 20 min    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn